WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
Transcriber: Sarah Braun
Reviewer: Denise RQ

00:00:15.542 --> 00:00:19.084
Wow, it's truly an honor
to be here with all of you.

00:00:19.085 --> 00:00:21.522
Today I want to share with you
why I believe

00:00:21.523 --> 00:00:25.521
that most entrepreneurs
are slowly killing themselves.

00:00:25.522 --> 00:00:26.826
If you're an entrepreneur,

00:00:26.827 --> 00:00:30.067
my intention is to help you achieve
greater results in your business

00:00:30.068 --> 00:00:32.762
by consistently performing
at a higher level,

00:00:32.762 --> 00:00:34.852
by being a lot less stressed out,

00:00:34.853 --> 00:00:38.117
and by having more fun
on your entrepreneurial journey.

00:00:38.118 --> 00:00:39.559
If you're not an entrepreneur,

00:00:39.560 --> 00:00:42.270
but you consider yourself
to be a hard worker in your job,

00:00:42.271 --> 00:00:44.978
I still think a lot of these principles
will apply to you.

00:00:44.979 --> 00:00:48.005
Entrepreneurs are a fascinating
breed of people.

00:00:48.006 --> 00:00:52.203
They're some of the most passionate
and driven people in the world.

00:00:52.204 --> 00:00:55.413
Oftentimes, they're also
some of the most obsessive

00:00:55.414 --> 00:00:59.991
and out of balance individuals
you'll ever meet.

00:00:59.992 --> 00:01:03.075
This combination can lead
to world changing innovation

00:01:03.076 --> 00:01:04.837
and incredible beauty.

00:01:04.837 --> 00:01:07.413
Unfortunately, it can also lead
to a lot of suffering

00:01:07.414 --> 00:01:09.791
and self destruction.

00:01:09.792 --> 00:01:12.138
Here's where this gets interesting.

00:01:12.139 --> 00:01:15.136
This personality issue that most
entrepreneurs have to deal with

00:01:15.137 --> 00:01:19.871
is strongly compounded
by a very dangerous social issue.

00:01:19.872 --> 00:01:22.805
In North America today,
the social narrative entrepreneurship

00:01:22.806 --> 00:01:25.898
tells us that, to be successful,
we have to be willing

00:01:25.899 --> 00:01:31.027
to sacrifice our health, our relationships
and even our emotional well-being.

00:01:31.042 --> 00:01:35.180
Simply put, we got to pay the price
if we want to be successful.

00:01:35.181 --> 00:01:37.246
When we look at some
of the most successful

00:01:37.247 --> 00:01:40.082
and most influential role models
of entrepreneurship today,

00:01:40.083 --> 00:01:42.463
it's pretty interesting what we see.

00:01:42.464 --> 00:01:44.668
Let's look at Elon Musk, for example.

00:01:44.701 --> 00:01:48.530
Elon Musk is the poster boy
for world changing entrepreneurship.

00:01:48.542 --> 00:01:52.126
Over the last year, he's co-founded
some of the most extraordinary companies

00:01:52.127 --> 00:01:54.412
like PayPal, SpaceX and Tesla.

00:01:54.413 --> 00:01:57.832
He's done so by per proudly working
a 100 hours per week.

00:01:57.833 --> 00:02:00.661
In a recent interview, when asked
what advice he would give

00:02:00.662 --> 00:02:05.466
to aspiring entrepreneurs,
Elon said, "Just work like hell.

00:02:05.467 --> 00:02:11.839
You just gotta put in 80 to 100 hours
per week, week after week."

00:02:11.840 --> 00:02:15.162
Now, to put this in perspective,
to work 80 a week,

00:02:15.163 --> 00:02:20.442
you have to work from 8am till 9pm
nonstop for six days a week.

00:02:20.443 --> 00:02:23.647
If you're really courageous
and you want to work 100 hours a week,

00:02:23.648 --> 00:02:28.081
you're looking at six days a week
doing 8am to 12.30am.

00:02:28.082 --> 00:02:29.935
That's past midnight.

00:02:29.936 --> 00:02:34.181
That certainly doesn't leave a lot of time
for things like sleep and exercise

00:02:34.182 --> 00:02:37.842
and spending time with loved ones,
which ironically enough are all activities

00:02:37.843 --> 00:02:40.756
that have been shown scientifically
to increase our happiness

00:02:40.757 --> 00:02:43.103
and our work performance.

00:02:43.104 --> 00:02:46.213
Working this much can lead
to a whole slew of problems.

00:02:46.214 --> 00:02:47.335
In the case of Elon,

00:02:47.336 --> 00:02:51.091
there's a darker side to the story
that not a lot of people know about.

00:02:51.092 --> 00:02:54.669
He's only 42, and he's already
divorced twice.

00:02:54.670 --> 00:02:57.759
He admits that he spends
very little time with his five children.

00:02:57.760 --> 00:03:02.534
When he's with them,
he's often responding to e-mail.

00:03:02.542 --> 00:03:06.653
Now, I'm not here to judge
Elon's lifestyle or decisions.

00:03:06.654 --> 00:03:10.339
But I do believe that before
we start to glorify or emulate someone,

00:03:10.340 --> 00:03:12.088
we should look at the whole picture.

00:03:12.089 --> 00:03:14.523
Not just our highlight real.

00:03:14.524 --> 00:03:16.615
I know this from experience:

00:03:16.616 --> 00:03:18.773
The extreme pursuit
of my entrepreneur dreams

00:03:18.774 --> 00:03:21.496
almost destroyed me - twice.

00:03:21.497 --> 00:03:22.890
Over the last twelve months,

00:03:22.891 --> 00:03:25.727
I figured out a way to have
greater results in my business,

00:03:25.728 --> 00:03:29.832
not by pushing harder and working more,
but by actually working less,

00:03:29.833 --> 00:03:33.809
by having more fun
and enjoying my life a lot more.

00:03:33.810 --> 00:03:37.329
I realised that the dichotomy
between achieving my greatest dreams

00:03:37.330 --> 00:03:41.296
and enjoying my life in this moment,
was actually a false one.

00:03:41.297 --> 00:03:43.531
For people like me
and many other entrepreneurs

00:03:43.532 --> 00:03:45.585
who have an overachieving personality,

00:03:45.586 --> 00:03:48.597
taking more time to relax
and appreciating life more

00:03:48.598 --> 00:03:52.720
can be the biggest catalyst
to bigger results.

00:03:52.721 --> 00:03:56.008
For some of you, this might sound crazy
and too good to be true.

00:03:56.009 --> 00:03:58.792
So let me tell you
how I came to this realization.

00:03:58.793 --> 00:04:01.025
Three years ago,
I launched my first business.

00:04:01.026 --> 00:04:03.539
My intention was to help people
build better habits,

00:04:03.540 --> 00:04:07.268
improve their mindset and do more
extraordinary things with their life.

00:04:07.269 --> 00:04:09.490
At first I was super enthusiastic.

00:04:09.491 --> 00:04:13.707
I was having the time of my life
and this was really fun.

00:04:13.708 --> 00:04:17.308
But as I became more successful
and as the business grew,

00:04:17.309 --> 00:04:21.245
my workload increased
and so did the complexity of my life.

00:04:21.245 --> 00:04:23.110
Not knowing what to do,

00:04:23.111 --> 00:04:26.196
I decided to see what other
successful entrepreneurs were doing.

00:04:26.197 --> 00:04:28.433
To see if I could learn from them.

00:04:28.434 --> 00:04:30.914
When I found out that Mark Zuckerberg

00:04:30.915 --> 00:04:34.201
spends routinely 16 hours a day
at the Facebook office,

00:04:34.202 --> 00:04:36.845
I figured he was probably
a good example to follow.

00:04:36.846 --> 00:04:40.367
I mean, things have worked out
pretty well for him in the last few years.

00:04:40.368 --> 00:04:43.170
From that point on,
whenever I ran into a problem,

00:04:43.171 --> 00:04:48.209
I would just unleash my inner Zuckerberg
and throw more hard work at the problem.

00:04:48.210 --> 00:04:51.298
If figured if I could just
work a little bit harder,

00:04:51.299 --> 00:04:54.414
be a little more productive,
then all my problems would go away,

00:04:54.415 --> 00:04:57.555
my business would thrive
and then I would be happy.

00:04:57.556 --> 00:04:59.321
Well, let me tell you:

00:04:59.322 --> 00:05:01.993
That approach did not work at all.

00:05:01.994 --> 00:05:04.497
Within a few months,
I'd run myself into the ground,

00:05:04.498 --> 00:05:06.256
I was stressed out of my mind

00:05:06.257 --> 00:05:08.793
and I felt like there must be
something wrong with me

00:05:08.794 --> 00:05:13.107
because I just wasn't able
to work as much as Mark Zuckerberg.

00:05:13.108 --> 00:05:15.704
To make things worse,
here I was running a business

00:05:15.705 --> 00:05:22.105
called "The Feel Good Lifestyle",
while feeling stressed out and exhausted.

00:05:22.106 --> 00:05:24.800
As you can imagine,
I was a little bit out of integrity,

00:05:24.801 --> 00:05:26.297
and I hated that.

00:05:26.298 --> 00:05:28.257
So I decided to do things differently.

00:05:28.258 --> 00:05:31.510
I decided to do a little experiment.

00:05:31.511 --> 00:05:35.188
I gave myself a 30 day
work less challenge.

00:05:35.209 --> 00:05:37.766
For 30 days, I intentionally
spend less time working

00:05:37.767 --> 00:05:40.520
and I reallocated the extra time
through doing things like

00:05:40.521 --> 00:05:43.071
spending time with my friends,
going in nature

00:05:43.072 --> 00:05:46.492
and going on more dates
with amazing women.

00:05:46.493 --> 00:05:49.254
Now, as you can imagine,
it was a very enjoyable month.

00:05:49.255 --> 00:05:51.429
(Laughter)

00:05:51.430 --> 00:05:54.207
Lo and behold something
unexpected happened;

00:05:54.208 --> 00:05:58.984
my business had its most profitable
month ever by more than 45%.

00:05:58.985 --> 00:06:00.188
How?

00:06:00.189 --> 00:06:02.416
For one, because I wasn't
working all the time,

00:06:02.417 --> 00:06:04.361
I had a lot more mental clarity.

00:06:04.362 --> 00:06:08.594
I was able to see opportunities clearly
and act on them decisively.

00:06:08.595 --> 00:06:12.301
My creativity was on a whole new level,
I had some of my best ideas ever

00:06:12.302 --> 00:06:16.014
and my team and I were able
to execute on them a lot faster.

00:06:16.015 --> 00:06:19.448
I learned to build systems,
I learned to delegate more

00:06:19.449 --> 00:06:22.806
and I learned to focus on a few things
that actually mattered.

00:06:22.807 --> 00:06:25.581
Over the next few months,
I was on this amazing trajectory

00:06:25.582 --> 00:06:27.345
and things were going really well.

00:06:27.346 --> 00:06:29.991
And then, something interesting happened.

00:06:29.992 --> 00:06:33.218
Because things were going so well,
more opportunities came my way,

00:06:33.219 --> 00:06:38.201
I said yes to more things and before long
I was falling back into my old patterns.

00:06:38.202 --> 00:06:40.608
We're working on all these
exciting opportunities,

00:06:40.609 --> 00:06:45.106
we're making such rapid progress,
all I wanted to do was work more.

00:06:45.107 --> 00:06:47.084
I was addicted to the dopamine rush

00:06:47.085 --> 00:06:50.339
I got from crossing things
off my to do list.

00:06:50.340 --> 00:06:55.785
I was totally high off of the idea
that I was achieving my biggest goals.

00:06:55.786 --> 00:06:59.131
But before long, the high began to fade.

00:06:59.132 --> 00:07:02.329
I started to feel like all I was doing
was run around all day,

00:07:02.330 --> 00:07:05.392
trying to keep 300 balls in the air.

00:07:05.393 --> 00:07:09.095
Deep down, I knew I wanted
to take a break, but I was terrified

00:07:09.096 --> 00:07:12.455
that if I did, the whole thing
would fall apart

00:07:12.456 --> 00:07:15.032
and my business would crumble.

00:07:15.033 --> 00:07:18.138
Here I was, the successful
young entrepreneur,

00:07:18.139 --> 00:07:21.489
suffocating under the weight
of my own ambitions.

00:07:21.501 --> 00:07:24.817
I didn't know what to do so I just
reverted back to my old humor

00:07:24.818 --> 00:07:28.291
I threw more hard work at the problem,
hoping it would solve everything.

00:07:28.292 --> 00:07:29.927
Well, it didn't.

00:07:29.928 --> 00:07:31.821
One day in the midst of all this chaos,

00:07:31.822 --> 00:07:34.429
I decided to go to a
sensory deprivation tank.

00:07:34.430 --> 00:07:37.188
For those of you who don't know,
a sensory deprivation tank

00:07:37.189 --> 00:07:39.896
is a tank that's half full with water,
with a lot of salt,

00:07:39.897 --> 00:07:42.191
where you can actually float
on top of the water,

00:07:42.192 --> 00:07:44.639
in total darkness, in total quietude.

00:07:44.640 --> 00:07:49.338
It's a great place to relax and to do
some deep reflection.

00:07:49.339 --> 00:07:53.770
That day, when I lay down to float,
I immediately felt this immense wave

00:07:53.771 --> 00:07:57.167
of fatigue surge through my body.

00:07:57.168 --> 00:07:58.700
I felt it all.

00:07:58.701 --> 00:08:04.376
All the stress, all the pressure,
all the discipline I'd imposed upon myself

00:08:04.377 --> 00:08:07.387
in my quest to build a next great company.

00:08:07.388 --> 00:08:09.119
I felt it.

00:08:09.120 --> 00:08:13.452
In that moment, the dam just broke.

00:08:13.453 --> 00:08:16.048
I started crying uncontrollably.

00:08:16.049 --> 00:08:18.845
For the next 30 minutes,
I just laid there,

00:08:18.846 --> 00:08:22.418
butt-naked in the dark,
crying my heart out.

00:08:22.430 --> 00:08:24.639
With no idea what the hell
was happening to me.

00:08:24.640 --> 00:08:26.089
(Laughter)

00:08:26.090 --> 00:08:31.549
I wasn't even sad, I was just completely
exhausted, emotionally drained.

00:08:31.550 --> 00:08:33.964
For the last three years
I'd pushed myself so hard,

00:08:33.965 --> 00:08:37.354
I'd take on so many challenges
and I'd overcome so many of my fears

00:08:37.355 --> 00:08:40.626
and insecurities along the way,
but I'd never given myself the time

00:08:40.626 --> 00:08:45.331
or the permission to actually recover
from all this madness.

00:08:45.332 --> 00:08:47.066
It's funny looking back,

00:08:47.067 --> 00:08:51.168
this whole time I thought I was doing
such a great job, when in reality,

00:08:51.169 --> 00:08:55.740
what I was actually doing
was slowly killing myself.

00:08:55.741 --> 00:08:58.603
And I know I'm not the only one.

00:08:58.604 --> 00:09:02.759
I was like the athlete who is so motivated
and training so hard for the Olympics,

00:09:02.760 --> 00:09:06.418
that he ends up overtraining
and injuring himself.

00:09:06.434 --> 00:09:09.020
Sometimes we can have
the best intentions in the world,

00:09:09.021 --> 00:09:12.199
but the extreme pursuit of our dreams
ends up destroying us.

00:09:12.200 --> 00:09:16.769
Physically, mentally and emotionally.

00:09:16.770 --> 00:09:19.307
So in that moment, I knew
I needed to radically alter

00:09:19.308 --> 00:09:21.327
my approach to entrepreneurship.

00:09:21.328 --> 00:09:22.654
So I slowed down.

00:09:22.655 --> 00:09:24.924
I temporarily skilled down
parts of the business

00:09:24.925 --> 00:09:27.367
and I started asking myself
the big questions like,

00:09:27.368 --> 00:09:33.082
"Who am I? Why am I doing all this?
What do I really want?"

00:09:33.083 --> 00:09:36.542
I scrapped the whole masterplan
and I decided to give myself time

00:09:36.546 --> 00:09:41.155
to realign with my purpose
and with my soul's desires.

00:09:41.156 --> 00:09:46.012
I decided to stop treating myself
like a machine and accept the fact

00:09:46.013 --> 00:09:48.006
that I'm just human.

00:09:48.007 --> 00:09:52.770
And sometimes, I just need to chill out,
just like everybody else.

00:09:52.771 --> 00:09:55.314
I decided to stop obsessing
about the future

00:09:55.315 --> 00:09:59.579
and about these big goals I had in mind
and to start appreciating all the beauty

00:09:59.580 --> 00:10:02.288
that's in my life right now.

00:10:02.289 --> 00:10:05.269
I made a very critical change
to my mindset.

00:10:05.270 --> 00:10:08.078
I let go of the idea
that the amount of success I get

00:10:08.079 --> 00:10:11.529
is directly correlated
to the numbers of hours I worked.

00:10:11.530 --> 00:10:13.587
I just let that go.

00:10:13.588 --> 00:10:17.041
And then, magic started to happen.

00:10:17.042 --> 00:10:19.494
If we zoom out of entrepreneurship
for just a second

00:10:19.495 --> 00:10:23.329
and we look at different fields,
we can get a very different perspective

00:10:23.330 --> 00:10:28.048
on what it takes to achieve sustainable,
extraordinary performances over time.

00:10:28.049 --> 00:10:30.351
Let's look at elite athletes for example.

00:10:30.352 --> 00:10:34.192
In a twelve-month year, elite athletes
go through four seasons;

00:10:34.193 --> 00:10:37.222
they have the pre-season/training camp,

00:10:37.223 --> 00:10:39.089
they have the regular season,

00:10:39.090 --> 00:10:40.622
they have the play-offs,

00:10:40.623 --> 00:10:43.720
and then, they have the off-season.

00:10:43.721 --> 00:10:46.638
We never question the fact
that the best athletes in the world

00:10:46.639 --> 00:10:48.505
take four months off a year to recover

00:10:48.506 --> 00:10:50.715
and build themselves
back up for the next year.

00:10:50.716 --> 00:10:55.646
But if an entrepreneur was to do that,
we would think they're crazy.

00:10:55.647 --> 00:10:58.322
Let's look at rock stars.

00:10:58.323 --> 00:11:00.309
They operate in a very different way.

00:11:00.310 --> 00:11:03.339
They're not concerned about
working slow and steady long hours,

00:11:03.340 --> 00:11:05.029
the way they structure their lives

00:11:05.030 --> 00:11:07.040
is that they prepare
for their performance,

00:11:07.041 --> 00:11:09.974
they perform, and then they recover.

00:11:09.975 --> 00:11:13.765
What would happen if as entrepreneurs,
instead of working all these long hours,

00:11:13.766 --> 00:11:16.681
we looked at our life in terms
of preparing for a performance,

00:11:16.682 --> 00:11:19.361
performing brilliantly
for just a few hours,

00:11:19.362 --> 00:11:22.031
and then recovering
until our next performance.

00:11:22.032 --> 00:11:24.661
What would that do for a business?

00:11:24.662 --> 00:11:27.259
And finally, if we look at artists,
like painters,

00:11:27.260 --> 00:11:29.422
they're not obsessed
about their productivity

00:11:29.423 --> 00:11:32.336
and how many hours they work,
what they focus on

00:11:32.337 --> 00:11:35.150
is getting in a state
of alignment and flow

00:11:35.151 --> 00:11:38.211
so that their greatest work can emerge.

00:11:38.212 --> 00:11:41.314
What would happen if as entrepreneurs,
we weren't so obsessed

00:11:41.315 --> 00:11:43.842
with the volume of our output
and the number of hours

00:11:43.843 --> 00:11:46.107
we put in the office, and instead,

00:11:46.108 --> 00:11:51.101
we focused on creating
the most amazing, beautiful work.

00:11:51.102 --> 00:11:53.213
What would that do?

00:11:53.214 --> 00:11:55.793
To give you an example
of these principles in action,

00:11:55.794 --> 00:12:00.358
this month my business is well on its way
to having another record month in profit.

00:12:00.359 --> 00:12:04.235
But we didn't do it by hustling harder
and pushing more.

00:12:04.236 --> 00:12:06.341
I actually spend
the first week of the month

00:12:06.342 --> 00:12:09.211
on a sailing trip of the coast
of California with my friends,

00:12:09.212 --> 00:12:10.709
totally disconnected from work.

00:12:10.710 --> 00:12:14.491
Actually, the only productive thing I did
was write this talk.

00:12:14.492 --> 00:12:17.179
The second week of the month
I worked about 30 hours.

00:12:17.180 --> 00:12:20.107
And yet, we're achieving
greater results than ever.

00:12:20.108 --> 00:12:21.659
It's a lot easier.

00:12:21.660 --> 00:12:26.064
And that feels really good,
especially after all the hard work.

00:12:26.065 --> 00:12:29.609
Now, I don't have all the answers
and this is a highly personal topic,

00:12:29.610 --> 00:12:32.439
it's different for me, and you,
and everybody else.

00:12:32.440 --> 00:12:36.567
Maybe for Elon Musk, working
a hundred hours a week really is optimal.

00:12:36.568 --> 00:12:40.679
Or maybe, he's not succeeding
because of his crazy work schedule.

00:12:40.680 --> 00:12:43.242
Or rather, in spite of it.

00:12:43.243 --> 00:12:45.698
Maybe Elon could be doing even better.

00:12:45.699 --> 00:12:46.587
I don't know.

00:12:46.588 --> 00:12:49.363
But what I do know is that one
of the most important traits

00:12:49.364 --> 00:12:50.666
of successful entrepreneurs

00:12:50.667 --> 00:12:53.612
is that we constantly
test our assumptions.

00:12:53.613 --> 00:12:55.277
So let me ask you this:

00:12:55.278 --> 00:12:57.043
What is your current assumption

00:12:57.044 --> 00:12:59.803
about the correlation between
the number of hours you work

00:12:59.804 --> 00:13:02.471
and the amount of success you'll have?

00:13:02.472 --> 00:13:05.675
Do you believe that you have to
push yourself to the limit each week

00:13:05.676 --> 00:13:07.942
in order to reach your goals?

00:13:07.943 --> 00:13:12.601
Or is it possible that maybe,
if you slow down a little bit,

00:13:12.602 --> 00:13:16.885
if you give yourself time to rest,
to reflect and to recover,

00:13:16.886 --> 00:13:22.940
not only you'd be happier and healthier,
but your business would be better as well?

00:13:22.941 --> 00:13:25.094
If you think that there's
even a remote chance

00:13:25.095 --> 00:13:28.905
that that might be the case,
I think we should test it.

00:13:28.906 --> 00:13:31.078
So here's my invitation to you:

00:13:31.079 --> 00:13:33.903
For the next 30 days,
starting on Monday morning,

00:13:33.904 --> 00:13:37.752
give yourself a 30 day
work less challenge.

00:13:37.753 --> 00:13:40.049
Whatever amount of work
you're currently doing,

00:13:40.050 --> 00:13:42.681
skill it down by 25%.

00:13:42.682 --> 00:13:46.275
So if you're currently working 80 hours,
skill it down to 60.

00:13:47.485 --> 00:13:50.941
If you're working 60 hours,
take it down to 45.

00:13:50.942 --> 00:13:53.551
And then, start to track the results.

00:13:53.552 --> 00:13:55.066
Look at the qualitative metrics

00:13:55.067 --> 00:13:58.997
like how you feel, how creative
and productive you're being,

00:13:58.998 --> 00:14:00.721
and look at the hard data,

00:14:00.722 --> 00:14:03.703
the quantitative metrics
like your profit and your revenue.

00:14:03.704 --> 00:14:06.070
See what happens.

00:14:06.071 --> 00:14:07.451
Worst case scenario:

00:14:07.452 --> 00:14:09.249
You'll have a really fun month,

00:14:09.250 --> 00:14:11.917
you'll get to experience life
in a whole different way,

00:14:11.918 --> 00:14:14.544
and you'll be a lot more rested
by the time you get back

00:14:14.584 --> 00:14:17.460
to the regular schedule next month.

00:14:17.495 --> 00:14:19.489
But best case scenario:

00:14:19.490 --> 00:14:22.129
You realised that this whole time
you've been the victim

00:14:22.130 --> 00:14:24.706
of a broken social narrative.

00:14:24.707 --> 00:14:28.849
And that you could actually
be more successful by working less.

00:14:28.850 --> 00:14:31.048
How cool would that be?

00:14:31.049 --> 00:14:34.581
A lot of successful entrepreneurs
are starting to make that shift,

00:14:34.584 --> 00:14:39.793
from Yvon Chouinard from Patagonia
to Tim Ferris and even Arianna Huffington.

00:14:39.785 --> 00:14:42.807
Maybe it's time for you
to make that shift as well.

00:14:42.808 --> 00:14:47.647
Whatever you decide to do,
here's the bottom line:

00:14:47.648 --> 00:14:49.793
Entrepreneurship does take
a lot of hard work.

00:14:49.794 --> 00:14:51.375
There's always going to be phases

00:14:51.376 --> 00:14:53.984
where we need to sprint
and put in longer hours.

00:14:53.985 --> 00:14:57.475
But trying to stay
in 'biz' mode all the time

00:14:57.476 --> 00:15:00.227
is one of the most
destructive things we can do.

00:15:00.228 --> 00:15:04.960
For our health, for our relationships,
and for our business.

00:15:04.961 --> 00:15:07.398
I sincerely believe that now,
more than ever,

00:15:07.399 --> 00:15:09.417
the world needs
its entrepreneurs to shine,

00:15:09.418 --> 00:15:13.204
if together, we're going to overcome
some of the world's biggest problems.

00:15:13.205 --> 00:15:14.655
But this isn't going to happen

00:15:14.656 --> 00:15:17.013
when entrepreneurs are
constantly exhausted

00:15:17.014 --> 00:15:19.282
and just running on fumes all the time.

00:15:19.292 --> 00:15:22.459
It's going to happen when entrepreneurs
are inspired and energized,

00:15:22.460 --> 00:15:25.928
because they're aligned
with the natural rhythm of their body.

00:15:25.929 --> 00:15:27.992
Here's the good news:

00:15:27.993 --> 00:15:33.289
From what I've learned, you don't need
to work yourself to death to succeed.

00:15:33.290 --> 00:15:37.030
But what you do need to do
is find the optimal rest for you.

00:15:37.031 --> 00:15:40.514
So that every day, you can bring
your greatest work to life.

00:15:40.515 --> 00:15:43.771
So that you can feel
totally and fully alive

00:15:43.772 --> 00:15:47.063
on the path to achieving your greatest
entrepreneurial dreams.

00:15:47.064 --> 00:15:48.277
Thank you.

00:15:48.278 --> 00:15:50.833
(Applause)

